1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,570
A young man told me how he concentrated on seeing the good side when he lost his job.

2
00:00:05,840 --> 00:00:07,570
He explained it this way.

3
00:00:08,080 --> 00:00:11,410
I was working for a large credit reporting company.

4
00:00:11,600 --> 00:00:14,290
One day I was given short notice to leave.

5
00:00:14,400 --> 00:00:20,929
There was an economy wave on, and they dismissed the employees who were least valuable to the company.

6
00:00:21,280 --> 00:00:26,770
The job didn't pay too well, but by the standards I grew up with, it was pretty good.

7
00:00:26,960 --> 00:00:33,969
I really felt terrible for a few hours, but then I decided to look at being bounced as a blessing in disguise.

8
00:00:34,160 --> 00:00:39,410
I really didn't like the job much, and had I stayed there, I'd never have gone far.

9
00:00:39,760 --> 00:00:43,410
Now I had a chance to find something I really liked to do.

10
00:00:43,679 --> 00:00:49,169
It wasn't long until I found a job that I liked a lot better that paid more money, too.

11
00:00:49,439 --> 00:00:53,969
Being fired from that credit company was the best thing that ever happened to me.

12
00:00:54,720 --> 00:00:59,489
Remember, you see in any situation what you expect to see.

13
00:00:59,840 --> 00:01:02,770
See the good side and conquer defeat.

14
00:01:03,120 --> 00:01:08,449
All things do work together for good if you'll just develop clear vision.

15
00:01:10,160 --> 00:01:18,290
In quick review, The difference between success and failure is found in one's attitudes toward setbacks,

16
00:01:18,320 --> 00:01:23,010
handicaps, discouragements, and other disappointing situations.

17
00:01:23,678 --> 00:01:30,050
Five guideposts to help you turn defeat into victory are 1.

18
00:01:30,320 --> 00:01:33,570
Study setbacks to pave your way to success.

19
00:01:33,679 --> 00:01:38,130
When you lose, learn, and then go on to win next time.

20
00:01:38,240 --> 00:01:39,889
2.

21
00:01:40,240 --> 00:01:43,489
Have the courage to be your own constructive critic.

22
00:01:43,679 --> 00:01:47,010
Seek out your faults and weaknesses and then correct them.

23
00:01:47,280 --> 00:01:49,250
This makes you a professional.

24
00:01:49,250 --> 00:01:51,169
3.

25
00:01:51,360 --> 00:01:52,929
Stop blaming luck.

26
00:01:53,360 --> 00:01:55,090
Research every setback.

27
00:01:55,200 --> 00:01:56,689
Find out what went wrong.

28
00:01:56,800 --> 00:02:01,410
Remember, blaming luck never got anyone where he wanted to go.

29
00:02:02,480 --> 00:02:06,130
Four, blend persistence with experimentation.

30
00:02:06,320 --> 00:02:10,370
Stay with your goal, but don't beat your head against a stone wall.

31
00:02:10,560 --> 00:02:13,090
Try new approaches, experiment.

32
00:02:14,320 --> 00:02:19,169
Five, remember, there is a good side in every situation.
